builtin_tools.description:
Manage long-term memory across sessions.
Actions:
- search: Semantic search over stored memories. Example: {"action":"search","query":"user preferences"}
- get: Retrieve a specific memory by ID. Example: {"action":"get","id":"abc-123"}
- put: Store a new memory. Example: {"action":"put","text":"User prefers dark mode","kind":"fact"}
Use this tool to recall prior context, user preferences, or previously learned information.
Search BEFORE answering questions about past conversations or user details.
